HEADWORD: Secreto-motory
<hw>Se*cre`to-mo"to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Causing secretion; -- said of nerves which go
to glands and influence secretion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secretory</ent>⟦br⟧
